<H3> <TI>   Rafsanjani, Brunei Sultan To Discuss Islamic Topics </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302202894 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1530 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302202894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Sir <PERSON>Hassanal Bolkiah</PERSON>, sultan of <LOCATION>Brunei 
Darussalam</LOCATION>, and his delegation arrived in <LOCATION>Tehran</LOCATION> <TIME>this evening</TIME>. 
Our correspondent reports: [passage omitted] 
  Upon his arrival to <LOCATION>Tehran</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Mr. Bolkiah</PERSON> said that the 
expansion of relations in all fields was the most important aim 
of his visit to our country. 
  <PERSON>Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani</PERSON> spoke on the visit of the sultan of 
<LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION>, saying: 
  [Begin <PERSON>Rafsanjani</PERSON> recording] <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> is an Islamic country, 
its people are committed Muslims, and its government and people 
are all Muslims and our brothers. 
  In our foreign policy we give priority to Islamic countries. 
I had asked the esteemed sultan of <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> to visit <LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION> to 
discuss common religious issues and the current situation in the 
world of Islam, which necessitates cooperation among Islamic 
countries. Also his excellency can become more familiar with 
<LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION> and we can get to know <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> better. We can also assess 
any kind of cooperation which may exist between us and <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION>. 
In any case, we believe that further cooperation among Islamic 
countries is in the interests of Muslims and their countries. 
We hope to pave the way for further cooperation and become 
closer to each other. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

