<H3> <TI>   Further Cooperation Welcomed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302234094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 2030 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0302234094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] During their talks <DATE>Thursday</DATE> <TIME>night</TIME> [3 <DATE>February</DATE>], the 
president of the Islamic Republic of <LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION> and the Sultan of 
<LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> discussed and exchanged views on the latest world 
developments, regional issues, and bilateral cooperation between 
<LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION>. 
  During the talks, <PERSON>Hashemi-Rafsanjani</PERSON> thanked <PERSON>Hassanal 
Bolkiah</PERSON> 
for visiting <LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION> and expressed the hope that mutual cooperation 
would further deepen in all cultural, political, economic and 
technical fields. 
  The president added: Our foreign policy gives a particular 
priority to cooperation with Islamic countries -- your country 
is one of them -- and that is a very good factor for the further 
expansion of cooperation between us. Hashemi-Rafsanjani added: 
We are aware of your satisfactory stances vis-a-vis the problem 
of <LOCATION>Bosnia-Herzegovina</LOCATION> at the <ORGANIZATION>Islamic Conference Organization</ORGANIZATION> 
[ICO]. We hope to be able to increase the <ORGANIZATION>ICO</ORGANIZATION> activities. 
  Our country's president pointed out the existence of the 
<ORGANIZATION>Association of South East Asian Nations</ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION>Economic 
Cooperation Organization</ORGANIZATION> in the two mainly Muslim regions, and 
described cooperation between <LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> as an effective 
factor that can contribute toward further cooperation between 
the two regions. 
  Hashemi-Rafsanjani also stressed the need for the two 
countries' cooperation in the oil and gas industries and 
announced <LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION>'s readiness to help <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> with its technical and 
scientific needs in those industries. The president also 
welcomed the two countries' cooperation in cultural and artistic 
fields. 
  Then the Sultan of <PERSON>Brunei Hassanal Bolkiah</PERSON>, thanked our 
country's president for his kind remarks and praised the certain 
and valuable status of the Islamic Republic of <LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION> at global 
levels and said: <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> has always supported <LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION>'s principled 
and progressive stance in international circles and believes 
itself in such stances. 
  He added: We cooperate very well within the <ORGANIZATION>ICO</ORGANIZATION> and the 
Non-Aligned Movement. We have always condemned the aggression 
against the Bosnian Muslims and are ready to help them. We are 
ready to cooperate in the oil and gas industries and hope to be 
able to witness the expansion of relations between the two 
countries in all fields, particularly cultural fields. 

</TEXT>

