<HL>
   Letters to the Editor:
   Here's a Rich One
</HL>
<DATE>
09/23/91
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15
</SO>
<RE>
BRUNEI (BX)
FAR EAST (FE)
</RE>
<LP>
   In regard to your Aug. 22 article calling the sultan of
Brunei the world's richest man: Here is a story that was told
to me by his relative, the sultan of Johor:
   Some months ago, the sultan of Brunei visited Barney's,
and selected a few suits and shirts. When he tried to pay
with his American Express traveler's checks, the cashier
requested a driver's license and two other forms of ID.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   When the sultan told her that he didn't have a driver's
license, she said, "Sorry, it's against store policy for me
to accept your check."
   At that moment, one of the sultan's quick-thinking
bodyguards presented the cashier with a <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> dollar (Guess
whose portrait is on the money?) and inquired, "Will you
accept this as a photo ID?"
   <LOCATION>Keith Green
   New York</LOCATION>
</TEXT>
