English 1130 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Following the opening of <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION>'s embassy in 
<LOCATION>Tehran</LOCATION>, (Haj Suhini Bin Haj Muhammad Hassan), that country's 
first charge d'affaires in the <LOCATION>Islamic Republic of Iran</LOCATION>, 
yesterday met with the Iranian foreign minister, <PERSON>Mr. Velayati</PERSON> 
and presented his credentials. 
  In the meeting, the two officials discussed the expansion 
and 
the strengthening of the two countries' relations, and the 
coming visit of the sultan of <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Haj Hassan Bolkiah</PERSON>, to 
<LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION>. 
  The Bruneian charge d'affaires considered the Islamic 
Republic of <LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION> as a second home, and stressed the willingness 
of his country's officials in strengthening relations with the 
Islamic Republic of <LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION>. 
  Pointing to the results of their previous meetings and 
discussions of the two countries' officials, and the positive 
steps which have been taken in line with the two countries' 
ties, <PERSON>Mr. Velayati</PERSON> considered the Bruneian ruler's coming visit 
to <LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION> as a significant step for expansion of relations. 
