<HEADLINE>
FT  22 DEC 94 / International Company News: 'No intention' to sell Plaza
stake, Trump says
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<PERSON>Mr Donald Trump</PERSON>, the <LOCATION>US</LOCATION> property developer, said yesterday he had no
intention of selling his 51 per cent stake in the landmark Plaza Hotel in
<LOCATION>New York</LOCATION>, but said his company had been approached by people interested in
acquiring a stake in the <LOCATION>Plaza</LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION>Reuter</ORGANIZATION> reports from <LOCATION>New York</LOCATION>.
<PERSON>Mr Trump</PERSON> told <ORGANIZATION>CNBC</ORGANIZATION> cable television that his company had had contacts with
the representative of the Sultan of <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION>, who is considered one of the
world's richest people.
'The Sultan of <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION>, his people have spoken to us, various other people
have spoken to us and we may do some kind of partnership or something,' <PERSON>Mr
Trump</PERSON> said.
The <ORGANIZATION>New York Post</ORGANIZATION> had earlier reported that the sultan and his partners had
bid more than Dollars 300m for the Fifth Avenue hotel.
However, <ORGANIZATION>Trump Organisation</ORGANIZATION> chief executive <PERSON>Mr Nicholas Ribis</PERSON> said there had
been no substantive discussions.
