<HEADLINE>
FT  11 FEB 92 / Sultan Of Brunei may buy 10 percent of PAL
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MANILA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Sultan of <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> is negotiating to buy 10 per cent of the equity of
<ORGANIZATION>Philippine Airlines</ORGANIZATION> (PAL), Reuter reports from <LOCATION>Manila</LOCATION>. The Philippine
government said the Sultan had reached agreement with the committee on
privatisation last week. A 67 per cent stake in <ORGANIZATION>PAL</ORGANIZATION> was awarded to a
consortium led by <ORGANIZATION>AB Capital and Investment Corporation</ORGANIZATION> at a <DATE>January 30</DATE>
auction.
