<HEAD>Sultan of Brunei Spends $950,000 on Birthday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Sultan of <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION>, one of the world's richest
men, reportedly spent at least <MONEY>$950,000</MONEY> on his nephew's ninth
birthday party.
   The <ORGANIZATION>Sunday Express</ORGANIZATION> said the sultan converted a ballroom at
<ORGANIZATION>Claridge</ORGANIZATION>'s in <LOCATION>London</LOCATION> into a replica of <ORGANIZATION>Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles</ORGANIZATION>
headquarters.
   An army of workers turned the ballroom into a giant <LOCATION>New York
City</LOCATION> sewer for the party for young <PERSON>Prince Bahar</PERSON>, the paper said.
Four men dressed as the superheros, <ORGANIZATION>Donatello</ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION>Leonardo</LOCATION>,
<PERSON>Michelangeo</PERSON> and <PERSON>Raphael</PERSON>, mingled with the young guests.
   A group of luxurious anterooms were transformed into a network
of gurglig drains, the paper said. Music was provided by the pop
duo Partners in <LOCATION>Kryme</LOCATION>, who were flown to <LOCATION>London</LOCATION> to perform their
hit ``Turtle Power,'' the newspaper said.
   Claridge's banqueting staff served pizza in a neon-lit pizza
parlor, <ORGANIZATION>The Sunday Express</ORGANIZATION> said. It did not say what day the party
took place.
   ``It was an incredible sight,'' said one member of <PERSON>Claridge</PERSON>'s
staff, who spoke to the newspaper on condition of anonymity.
   The report could not be independently confirmed.
</TEXT>
