  [Text] <LOCATION>Thailand</LOCATION> has reaffirmed its readiness to fully 
cooperate with <LOCATION>Brunei Darussalam</LOCATION> in various areas both under 
bilateral relation and within the <ORGANIZATION>ASEAN</ORGANIZATION> framework. Bruneian 
Foreign Minister <PERSON>Prince Mohamed Bolkiah</PERSON> held talks with Prime 
Minister <PERSON>Chuan Likphai</PERSON> on <DATE>Friday</DATE> on bilateral cooperation. He 
concluded his three-day visit to <LOCATION>Thailand</LOCATION> yesterday. 
  Prime Minister <PERSON>Chuan</PERSON> said he hoped that <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> would 
increase 
its investment in the region. He also expressed his 
appreciation to the Bruneian Government for taking good care of 
Thai workers in that country. The Bruneian foreign minister 
praised Thai workers for their efficiency, saying that <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> is 
still in need of foreign labor as the country is accelerating 
the construction of infrastructure. He said <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> would learn 
from successes in national development in various countries, 
<LOCATION>Thailand</LOCATION> included. The country will host the next <ORGANIZATION>ASEAN</ORGANIZATION> 
ministerial meeting after <LOCATION>Thailand</LOCATION>. 
  Both sides will work out the program for the visit to 
<LOCATION>Thailand</LOCATION> by <PERSON>Sultan Haji Hassanal Bolkiah</PERSON> of <LOCATION>Brunei</LOCATION> as guest of 
His Majesty the King of <LOCATION>Thailand</LOCATION>. 

</TEXT>

